# Cursor Rules for Advertising Video Editing Course

## Video Embedding

### YouTube Videos
Use the `video-player` include with the following pattern:

```liquid
{% include video-player.html
   platform="youtube"
   id="VIDEO_ID"
   title="Descriptive Video Title"
   timestamps="0:00|Label1,1:30|Label2,3:45|Label3" %}
```

**Rules:**
- Always use `platform="youtube"` for YouTube videos
- Extract video ID from URL: `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID` → use `VIDEO_ID`
- Always provide a descriptive `title` for accessibility
- Add timestamps for videos longer than 2 minutes or when specific moments need highlighting
- Timestamp format: `"MM:SS|Label"` or `"HH:MM:SS|Label"`, comma-separated
- Place videos at the beginning of relevant sections, before explanatory text

**Example:**
```liquid
{% include video-player.html
   platform="youtube"
   id="dQw4w9WgXcQ"
   title="Example Video Title"
   timestamps="0:00|Introduction,2:15|Main Content,5:30|Conclusion" %}
```

### Vimeo Videos
Use the same pattern but with `platform="vimeo"`:

```liquid
{% include video-player.html
   platform="vimeo"
   id="VIDEO_ID"
   title="Descriptive Video Title"
   timestamps="0:00|Label1,1:30|Label2" %}
```

**Rules:**
- Extract video ID from URL: `https://vimeo.com/123456789` → use `123456789`
- Same timestamp format as YouTube
- Same placement rules

### Video Placement Guidelines
- Place videos at the start of relevant theory sections (before "Key Thesis" or main content)
- Add context before the video embed (brief description)
- Follow with analysis/discussion points after the video
- Use timestamps to highlight key moments mentioned in the text

