## Image Embedding

### Semantic Image Structure
Use semantic HTML5 `<figure>` and `<figcaption>` elements:

```html
<figure class="spectacle-image">
<img src="IMAGE_URL" alt="Descriptive alt text" loading="lazy" />
<figcaption>
<p>Image caption describing what the image shows and its relevance to the content.</p>
<p class="image-credit">Photographer/Source Credit</p>
</figcaption>
</figure>
```

**Rules:**
- Always use `<figure>` wrapper for images with captions
- Always include descriptive `alt` text for accessibility
- Always use `loading="lazy"` for performance
- Include caption in first `<p>` tag within `<figcaption>`
- Include credit in second `<p>` tag with class `image-credit`
- Place images after video embeds but before main content text
- Use descriptive class names (e.g., `spectacle-image`, `theory-image`)

**Example:**
```html
<figure class="theory-image">
<img src="https://example.com/image.jpg" alt="Description of image content" loading="lazy" />
<figcaption>
<p>Caption explaining the image and its relevance to the lesson content.</p>
<p class="image-credit">Photographer Name/Source</p>
</figcaption>
</figure>
```

### Image Placement Guidelines
- Place images after video embeds in the same section
- Position before "Key Thesis" or main explanatory text
- Use images to illustrate theoretical concepts visually
- Ensure images support and enhance the text content

