## Content Structure Pattern

### Standard Section Layout
When adding media to a lesson section, follow this order:

1. **Section Title** (e.g., `#### 1. Theory Name`)
2. **Video Embed** (if applicable)
3. **Image** (if applicable)
4. **Key Thesis/Introduction Text**
5. **Main Content**
6. **Examples/Discussion Points**

**Example:**
```markdown
#### 1. Theory Name

{% include video-player.html
   platform="youtube"
   id="VIDEO_ID"
   title="Video Title"
   timestamps="0:00|Intro" %}

<figure class="theory-image">
<img src="IMAGE_URL" alt="Alt text" loading="lazy" />
<figcaption>
<p>Caption</p>
<p class="image-credit">Credit</p>
</figcaption>
</figure>

**Key Thesis:**
Main content here...
```

